Recycled Claim Standard 100

Recycled Claim Standard 100 (RCS100) certified products contain recycled content (>95%) that has been independently verified at each stage of the supply chain, from the source to the final product. The purchase of Recycled Claim Standard (RCS) certified products demonstrates demand for recycled materials. A product must contain at least 50% certified RCS100 material to qualify for Climate Pledge Friendly.

About this item

  • SWISS NON-STICK COATING - Switzerland ILAG nonstick coating, PFOA free, safe and healthy.
  • WOODGRAIN BAKELITE HANDLE - The bakelite handle features woodgrain design, it is comfortable to grip and stays cool while cooking. Oven safe to 302F.
  • HIGH MAGNETIC CONDUCTIVE BASE - High magnetic conductive stainless steel base. The nonstick skillet bottom is flat and thick, which helps distribute heat evenly and quickly. Suitable for all stove, including induction cooktop.
  • STURDY BODY - The non sticking omelet pan inside is made of cast aluminum, which is more sturdy and long-lasting. SENSARTE non-stick frying pan is passed international certification.
  • EASY TO CLEAN - Super easy to clean up, just wipe it with a paper towel or rinse it with water. Dishwasher safe.

Nonstick pan with Swiss nonstick coating

Merchant Video

20 Years of Premium Quality, Specializing in Nonstick Cookware

Previous page
Next page

Featuring 3rd-generation Swiss granite coating, this pan is ultra non-stick, long-lasting, and requires less oil for flavorful meals. It stays like new over time and cleans effortlesslyjust wipe or rinse. Cooking made easy and enjoyable.

NOTE: Minor scratches on the stainless steel base are normal due to factory polishing. SENSARTE provides 100% brand-new pans.

Next page

Use And Care

Stay away from metal utensil in cooking as well as steel wool balls when cleaning.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

Customers say

Customers find the frying pan to be of good quality, easy to clean, and appreciate its great non-stick surface that works like a cast iron pan. Moreover, they consider it a good value for money and like its appearance. However, customers disagree on the pan's durability, with some reporting that the non-stick surface peels off after about a year. Additionally, there are mixed experiences with food sticking to the pan.

Amazon Customer
5 out of 5 stars
Light weight, induction-ready, slick pan. Includes screwdriver to attach handle.
I got this to replace an old Teflon IKEA pan that started peeling. This is a nice upgrade. We needed something light weight and works on induction stove, and this works great. This 9-inch pan is just right to fry two eggs, or make a small omelette. Sometimes we use it for sausages or frying some vegetables. Other reviews mention having to attach the handle. I was pleasantly surprised to find a decent quality screw driver that fits the screw perfectly. I just lined it up and screwed it together with tight pressure, but not so much to strip the screw threads. The handle is a solid fit and feels good in the hand. It has no lid, which I did not expect. Instructions say to avoid using metal tools or metal SOS scrubbing pads. We use silicon spatulas and scrub brushes which work fine. Overall, I would say it's a good deal and perfect for our needs.

  • S. Taggart
    4.0 out of 5 stars Very slow to heat and cool with using on induction cooktops
    Reviewed in the United States on September 21, 2025
    Size: 11 InchColor: GrayVerified Purchase
    MY COMMENTS APPLY TO INDUCTION STOVETOP COOKING:

    First, these are well made pans. They are very heavy aluminum with stainless bottoms (not solid stainless on the bottom but some kind of small pieces laminated in). The handles are excellent (some kind of faux wood plastic) and feel good in your hand (you have to install the handle with the free screwdriver included). I have one big complaint with these pans (I have the 9.5, 11 and 12.5"): they are VERY slow to heat and react on an induction stove top. Because they are such thick aluminum (especially compared to a normal stainless pan), it takes much longer to heat the pan and correspondently, to cool it when you turn the induction heat down. With my other pans, they get very hot within seconds when heat is applied (induction, that is) and when heat/induction is turned down, the react almost instantly. Not so these pans: to heat a small amount of water (as a test) and take up to a minute (when it might take half that or less with all stainless). Worse, instead of 1 or 2 seconds to cool when heat is removed, these pans "coast" for a long time as the thick aluminum cools. This means you will have to change some of your "usual" cooking techniques with these compared to other cookware you have. This might be a positive attribute for some cooking situations but buyers should be aware that these pans will behave quite differently when compared to traditional cookware on an induction top.
